Today, Saturday, July 16, is the D-Day for the Osun State Gubernatorial Election, in Osun State, South-West Nigeria, with the incumbent Governor Gboyega Oyetola, vying to stay in office for another four-year tenure while 15 others compete to replace him as the Chief Executive of the State. The 15 contenders include Akinade Akanmu Ogunbiyi, representing the Accord Party; the African Action Congress candidate is Awojide Peter Segun; Kehinde Munirudeen Olumuyiwa A Atanda is bearing the flag of the Action Democratic Party; Adegboyega Isiaka Oyetola for the APC; the Allied Peoples Movement presented Awoyemi Oluwatayo Lukuman; Adebayo Adeolu Elisha for the All People’s Party; Adeleke Adesoji Masilo Aderemi Adedapo for the Boot Party; Yussuff Sulaimon Lasun, Labour Party; Rasaq Oyelami Saliu for the New Nigeria Peoples Party; National Rescue Movement has Abede Adetona Samuel as its flagbearer; PDP has Adeleke Ademola Jackson Nurudeen as its flagbearer; Peoples Redemption Party: Ayowole Olubusuyi Adedeji; Social Democratic Party: Omigbodun Oyegoke Akinrinola; Young Progressives Party: Ademola Bayonle Adeseye; and Zenith Labour Party: Adesuyi John Olufemi. They are 1. Adegboyega Oyetola of the APC. He promised that if re-elected, he would reinforce the state security system and empower the police force. 5 . Akin Ogunbiyi of the Accord Party. Akin Ogunbiyi has promised to bring businesses and investments that would boost the state’s economy and create jobs for the youth. Follow this thread for results, and update from the Osun State governorship election. #Osundecides2022.